Observations
Transfer learning did not always outperform custom CNNs.
EfficientNetB0 achieved the best balance between accuracy and class-wise performance.
Left and Right orientations were easier to classify than Bottom orientations.
The Bottom class consistently produced lower F1 scores across models, indicating higher confusion.
Data augmentation improved generalization and reduced overfitting.
Conclusion

Among all evaluated models, EfficientNetB0 produced the best overall results with 78.95% accuracy and 77.67% Macro F1 score. Although CNN_V3 achieved identical accuracy, EfficientNetB0 provided slightly better class-balanced performance. Therefore, EfficientNetB0 was selected as the final model for capacitor polarity classification in the proposed PCB-AI system.

